At Ironbridge Gorge, we fire up memories of the Industrial Revolution. And all along the way, we'll be driving on the left and polishing our pub etiquette.(n)

programme.title: Rick Steves' Europe
programme.desc: Lisbon, built with the riches of Portugal's New World discoveries, has a rustic charm. We'll remember great navigators, eat lots of cod, enjoy pastries hot out of the oven, stroll the city's back lanes and its reinvigorated waterfront, marvel at an exquisite church built with spice taxes, and enjoy some soulful fado music. Then we'll side-trip to Sintra to explore the fanciful castles of Portuguese royalty and climb hilltop ramparts with grand views.(n)

programme.title: Rick Steves' Europe
programme.desc: Portugal has an oversized history, fascinating culture, and boatloads of sardines. Saving the capital city of Lisbon for another episode, we'll dance on the beach at Nazaré, marvel at a medieval abbey in Batalha, visit a royal library and revel with university students in Coimbra, savor port wine with the people who made it along the Douro River, and get to know Portugal's gritty and fascinating second city, Porto.(n)

programme.title: Rick Steves' Europe
programme.desc: Setting sail on the Mediterranean, we'll explore the ins and outs and pros and cons of cruising. We'll learn how to get the most out of a cruise and exercise our independence to make smart use of limited time on shore by planning well, avoiding lines, and eating quick-but-local meals on the go. Along with the joys and efficiencies of cruising, we'll consider the downsides, including the inevitable congestion and commercialism that comes with mass tourism.(n)

programme.title: The Luck of the Irish

programme.title: The Leopard Man

programme.title: The Three Musketeers
programme.desc: A comedic take on the classic tale of French swordsmen who face off against an evil Cardinal.

programme.title: The Mark of Zorro
programme.desc: The son of an aristocrat in 19th-century California dons a mask to help fight for the downtrodden people oppressed by a wicked governor. Complicating matters is the vigilante's affections for the governor's beautiful niece. (Repeat).

programme.title: Batman
programme.desc: Batman and Robin are called in as a last resort when the criminal masterminds of the millennium team up to conquer Gotham City by turning the U.N. Security Council into dust. (Repeat).

programme.title: Fathom
programme.desc: A skydiver agrees to help a Scottish colonel seeking to recover an atomic device in Spain. (Repeat).

programme.title: Jumpin' Jack Flash
programme.desc: A computer operator accidentally interfaces with a British espionage agent. (Repeat).

programme.title: Eyewitness
programme.desc: A janitor is infatuated with a television reporter, and when she arrives at his building to interview the tenants about a murder that's occurred on the premises, the janitor, having discovered the body, implies that he knows more than he's saying in order to keep the newswoman interested in him. (Repeat).

programme.title: Siberia
programme.desc: Lucas, a diamond trader who travels to Saint Petersburg to arrange a sale, discovers that his Russian business partner has left his hotel and gone to a small Siberian village, so Lucas also heads there to try find him.

programme.title: The Lawnmower Man
programme.desc: Experimenting with pills and computer-simulated training regiments, an eccentric doctor uses his simpleton landscaper as his test subject. As the once simple man grows more intelligent, he comes to realize the advantage that has been taken of him and starts plotting his revenge. (Repeat).

programme.title: Saturn 3
programme.desc: A space station is disrupted by a visitor from Earth. Farrah Fawcett, Kirk Douglas, Harvey Keitel, Douglas Lambert. Harding: Ed Bishop. Crewman: Christopher Muncke. Stanley Donen directed.

programme.title: Frankenstein Meets the Space Monster
programme.desc: A robot named Frank must defeat Martians. (Repeat).

programme.title: Fiend Without a Face
programme.desc: Creatures nourished by atomic energy terrorize a community. Marshall Thompson. Chester: Terence Kilburn. Barbara: Kim Parker. Warren: Gil Winfield. Butler: Stanley Maxted. Directed by Arthur Crabtree. (Repeat).

programme.title: The Day the Earth Stood Still
programme.desc: Washington, D.C., is visited by a pacifist outer-space alien and his impressive robot who demand the human race end aggression and warfare. (Repeat).

programme.title: The Day Mars Invaded Earth

programme.title: Invaders from Mars

programme.title: The Thing From Another World
programme.desc: A team of scientists at an Arctic research station near the crash site of a UFO unearth a mysterious figure frozen in ice, and when it thaws the unearthly monster goes on a murderous rampage. Remade by John Carpenter in 1982. (Repeat).

programme.title: The Crawling Eye
programme.desc: About a tentacled monster that lies in a radioactive cloud, waiting to strike. Forrest Tucker, Janet Munro. Directed by Quentin Lawrence.

programme.title: The Blob
programme.desc: A young couple is able to escape an alien life form whose jelly-like appearance keeps mysteriously growing. The teens discover the extra-terrestrial blob is getting bigger by devouring people, and they must do all they can to get the authorities to take action and save the rest of the town before it's too late. (Repeat).

programme.title: Galaxy of Terror
programme.desc: Astronauts try to rescue a marooned spaceship. Edward Albert, Erin Moran, Ray Walston. Baelon: Zalman King. Ilvar: Bernard Behrens. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Inseminoid
programme.desc: Explorers on a desolate planet find themselves in the middle of a nightmare when a crew member, Sandy, becomes impregnated by a monstrous alien creature. Sandy goes insane and begins to murder the crew one by one with superhuman strength. Also known as "Inseminoid.".(n)

programme.title: The Terror Within
programme.desc: The spawn of a deadly creature threatens to eliminate the people left on Earth after a deadly virus wipes out mankind, leaving the survivors to make a society underground. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Terror Within II
programme.desc: A futuristic hero who helps defend a laboratory from a mutant horde. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Whirlpool

programme.title: The Night Holds Terror
programme.desc: Taut thriller about three hoodlums holding a family at bay. Reminiscent of "The Desperate Hours." Jack Kelly. Doris: Hildy Parks. Batsford: John Cassavetes. Gosset: Vince Edwards. Logan: David Cross. Plenty of suspense. Andrew L. Stone directed. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Stranger on the Third Floor
programme.desc: An aspiring journalist testifies he saw a young man at the scene of a brutal killing and the man is sentenced to death. The journalist worries he is responsible for the death of an innocent man and begins his own investigation with his wife, but the duo soon find themselves threatened by a mysterious stranger. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Raw Deal

programme.title: The Man Who Watched the Trains Go By

programme.title: Cry of the City

programme.title: Please Murder Me
